@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api

### 1. Authenticate / Login as Admin to get Admin JWT
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### Save Admin JWT Token variable from response
@adminToken = {{login.response.body.token}}


### 2. Fetch Customer List (Default Page 1, Limit 10)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/customers
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json


### 3. Fetch Customer List Filtered by VIPs
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/customers?filter=VIP
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json


### 4. Fetch Customer List Sorted by Order Volume
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/customers?sort=most_orders
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json


### 5. Fetch Customer Directory Analytics Summary
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/customers/analytics
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json


### 6. Fetch Specific Customer Detail Profile (Jassim Al-Thani, ID 2)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/customers/2
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json


### 7. Fetch Customer Orders History (Filter by completed)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/customers/2/orders?page=1&limit=5&status=completed
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json


### 8. Block Customer Account (ID 2)
# @name blockCustomer
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/admin/customers/2/status
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "BLOCKED"
}


### 9. Verify Login Block Enforcement (Should return 403 Forbidden)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jassim.althani@gmail.com",
  "password": "Customer123!"
}


### 10. Restore Customer Account to ACTIVE (ID 2)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/admin/customers/2/status
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "ACTIVE"
}
